'''''Mini-Putt''''' is a simulation of [[miniature golf]] developed by [[Artech Digital Entertainment]] and released by [[Accolade (company)|Accolade]] for the [[Commodore 64]], [[MS-DOS]], [[Nintendo Entertainment System|NES]] and [[ZX Spectrum]] in 1987, and [[Apple IIGS]] in 1988.

==Gameplay==
''Mini-Putt'' is a miniature golf game featuring a variety of courses including traps and ricochets, and unusual gradations on the greens.<ref name="Dragon131"/>

==Reception==
